        "subject": "LU-18876 build: de-autotool the Lustre Makefiles",
        "message": "LU-18876 build: de-autotool the Lustre Makefiles\n\nWe can use plain Makefiles for the Lustre kernel build.\nRather than including Rules in each Makefile.in, we can\nset the cflags globally in the top-level Makefile. This\nallows us to remove the explicit INCLUDE_RULES in each\nMakefile.in. Also - define proper CONFIG options for\nuse in these Makefiles.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: I54506899f95cfc4b654817919bf7b46f2b3a15f5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64023\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\n"
      },
